Gunmen have kidnapped Mrs. Chidiebere Onyia, a female reporter of the Nigerian Television Authority (NTA), Port Harcourt, Rivers State. It was gathered that Onyia, a mother of three, was whisked away to an unknown place by her assailants on Tuesday evening while returning from work. Onyia was said to be conveying some of her colleagues in her car to their destinations at about 6.30pm when the hoodlums blocked her vehicle in the Woji area of Port Harcourt, seized her and zoomed off. Sources said the hoodlums fired gunshots into the air forcing people to runÂ  in different directions. Police spokesman Nnamdi Omoni said the police were on the hunt for her abductors.